I read this doc:
https://docs.flutter.dev/deployment/android#what-are-the-supported-target-architectures

Flutter does not currently support building for x86 

So, i add this into my product:

defaultConfig {
        ...

        ndk {
            abiFilters 'arm64-v8a', 'armeabi-v7a', 'x86_64'
        }
    }

@EarningsCall 
i mean:
Flutter haven't support AOT for x86 (32 bit) yet.

I had resolved the issue by inserting this lines into my build.gradle:
```
android {
  //...
  defaultConfig {
    ndk {
      // Filter for architectures supported by Flutter.
      abiFilters 'armeabi-v7a', 'arm64-v8a', 'x86_64'
    }
  }
}
```
